## Factory Pattern for App

```python
from flask import Flask


def create_app() -> Flask:
    app = Flask(__name__)
    app.config.from_prefixed_env()

    # dependency composition
    session = create_session(app.config["DATABASE_URL"])
    repository = SQLAlchemyResourceRepository(session)
    resource_service = ResourceService(repository)

    from resource.router import create_resource_bp
    app.register_blueprint(create_resource_bp(resource_service))

    return app
```

## Conventions
- Service receives dependencies via constructor (no decorators)
- Manual composition in `create_app()` factory (composition root)
- Repository interface via `ABC` for decoupling
- Custom domain errors (don't use HTTP errors)
- Service doesn't know Flask (no request/response)
- One service per domain, single-responsibility methods
- Type hints on all public methods
